cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with computer vision and deep learning-based approaches for intrinsic image decomposition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and supervised loss layers, which are common in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions benchmarks and evaluation metrics, which are often used in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) research.
